## TASK 6 — Fix the AppErrorBoundary console.error leak

**File:** `src/App.tsx`, line ~28

```typescript
componentDidCatch(error: Error, info: ErrorInfo) {
  console.error('App crashed:', error, info)  // ← this is the only console call in the app
}
```

In production, `console.error` leaks internal error details to the browser console. Replace with a no-op or a proper error reporting hook:

```typescript
componentDidCatch(error: Error, _info: ErrorInfo) {
  // In production, send to your error tracking service here
  // e.g. Sentry.captureException(error)
  if (import.meta.env.DEV) {
    console.error('App crashed:', error, _info)
  }
}
```

This keeps dev DX intact while being clean in production.

