## TASK 7 — Add GitHub Actions CI for tests

**Why:** The repo has a `react-doctor` workflow but no test runner CI. Tests should run on every push and PR.

**Create:** `.github/workflows/ci.yml`

```yaml
name: CI

on:
  push:
    branches: [main]
  pull_request:
    branches: [main]

jobs:
  test:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - uses: actions/setup-node@v4
        with:
          node-version: 20
          cache: npm
      - run: npm ci
      - run: npm test
      - run: npm run build
        env:
          VITE_SUPABASE_URL: ${{ secrets.VITE_SUPABASE_URL || 'https://placeholder.supabase.co' }}
          VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY: ${{ secrets.VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY || 'placeholder' }}
```

