## TASK 11 — Add `aria-label` to icon-only buttons

**Why:** There are several icon-only buttons in the editor (mode rail, toolbar actions) with no accessible label. This is a real accessibility gap.

**How to find them:**
```bash
grep -rn "onClick\|button" src/components/ModeRail.tsx src/layouts/EditorLayout.tsx | grep -v "aria-label"
```

For every `<button>` that contains only an icon (no visible text), add `aria-label`:

```tsx
// Before
<button onClick={handlePrint}>
  <Printer className="w-4 h-4" />
</button>

// After
<button onClick={handlePrint} aria-label="Print resume">
  <Printer className="w-4 h-4" />
</button>
```

Also ensure modals have `role="dialog"` and `aria-labelledby` pointing to their heading.

